Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
restorePowerSwitch(25.10)                            restorePowerSwitch(25.10)

Name
       restorePowerSwitch  -  Restores  the  information  stored  in the power
       switch databases

Syntax
        restorePowerSwitch

       [-help]

       [-file <string>]

       Restores the information stored in the power switch databases. You  can
       use  this  command to load back the power switch information only after
       completing power switch insertion using the addPowerSwitch command  and
       then saving the database information using the savePowerSwitch command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each restorePowerSwitch  parameter.  For  a  de-
              tailed  description  of  the command and all its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man restorePowerSwitch

       -file <string>
              Specifies the name of the file from which the power switch data-
              base information will be restored.

Related Information
              * addPowerSwitch

              * savePowerSwitch

